Thought: I'll start by fetching the security incident record that represents the password spray attack on 2024-07-18 from IP 170.54.121.63. Then I can extract its related AlertIds (which should reference alerts such as the email alert we’re interested in). Once I have those email alerts, I can join the email post-delivery records (which flag removals) to the initial email event records (that record senders) using the common field InternetMessageId. In this way I can determine the sender of the malicious email that was later removed.
Action: execute[
-- Step 1: Identify the incident record for the password spray attack.
SELECT * 
FROM SecurityIncident 
WHERE TimeGenerated LIKE '2024-07-18%' 
  AND Description LIKE '%password spray%'
  AND AdditionalData LIKE '%170.54.121.63%';
];
